<h2 class="wp-block-nbc-section-heading">Try a scam-blocking app</h2>



<p>Scam-blocking apps may help. Before you download, though, check reviews and read the fine print, De Leon warned.</p>



<p>“Double-check the privacy polices of these apps. They may be using your data, selling it, or they may be using it in ways you’re not comfortable with,” he said.</p>



<p>Finally: Sign up for the <a href="https://www.donotcall.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">National Do Not Call Registry</a>. You can do so online or by phone via the FTC.</p>



